I read the beginning of this post and started scanning when it started turning into a contest to see who can be the wittiest and fling the most creative 4-letter word.  I have no consolation for what you are going through and can offer you nothing more than the equivilent of a hug and the reassurance that not all men are like that (obviously).  I don't believe in the traditional form of christianity, but I do think there is an existance beyond this one.  The man had problems, and,yes, as Ishkur pointed out in one of the last posts I actually read, he took the coward's way out.  As much as I would love to know he had to live in torment for his actions, such is not the case.  Perhaps the tales of a punitive afterlife are true and he is burning eternally in a super-natural torture chamber, perhaps he is part of a conciousness that is not even aware of such posibilities.  Either way, I am sure your son needs you right now, as you probably need him.  He is six years old, so for him, this will soon be a sad memory, but for you, the loss will linger considerably longer.  Still, you do have the power to reduce the sting.  <br>
I hate to be trite, but life is short.  Actions like this just remind us how short life can be.  There are several lessons I could point to, but I have no intention of doing so.  It will pass, your son will make new friends, and this may later be something in his life's memories that reminds him of the way he does NOT want to be.  <br>
I know you need to vent, I have been in similar situations myself.  I, for one, invite you to vent until it gets easier for you to handle, but also remind you to give a big FUCK YOU to anyone that thinks &quot;she got what she deserved.&quot;  Sadly, things like this happen, they just do.  It doesn't mean we have to accept it, nor does it mean that it is any less tragic, but to stereo-type the people it happens to as &quot;Jerry Springer Episodes&quot; is just short-sighted and ignorant.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=316564" target="top">Tib</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
